# Multi-Tenant Security

## The isolation contract

Every data access must satisfy ALL of:
1. `org_id` comes from the verified auth token, never from the request body or URL
2. `org_id` is always present in WHERE clauses for DB queries
3. Redis keys always include `org_id` as the second segment
4. gRPC calls propagate `org_id` from the verified token, not from request fields

## org_id from token, not from request — always

```go
// WRONG — org_id from request body; caller can spoof any org
func handleListAgents(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    var req struct { OrgID uuid.UUID `json:"org_id"` }
    json.Decode(r.Body, &req)
    agents := store.List(ctx, req.OrgID) // can be any org!
}

// RIGHT — org_id extracted from verified token claims by middleware
func handleListAgents(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    orgID := middleware.OrgIDMust(r.Context()) // set by AuthMiddleware from token
    agents := store.List(ctx, orgID)
}
```

## PERMISSION_DENIED on cross-tenant miss, NOT NOT_FOUND

This rule is restated here because it is the most commonly violated rule in multi-tenant systems. Returning 404 for a cross-tenant resource access teaches attackers which resource IDs exist in other orgs.

```text
Attacker: GET /v1/agents/org-b-agent-uuid  (with org A token)
WRONG response: 404 Not Found  ← attacker knows the UUID is valid but in another org
RIGHT response: 403 Forbidden  ← attacker learns nothing
```

## Verify tenant at every layer — do not rely on a single check

```text
HTTP Handler: AuthMiddleware sets org_id from token ✓
gRPC Handler: Validates org_id in request matches auth context ✓
Store layer:  org_id in WHERE clause ✓
Database:     RLS policy enforces org_id ✓
```

Each layer is a defence. If any layer is missing, the next one catches it. No single point of failure.

## Tenant context propagation in gRPC

```go
// When proxy calls auth via gRPC, propagate org_id in metadata
// so auth service can include it in audit logs
ctx = metadata.AppendToOutgoingContext(ctx,
    "x-ibex-org-id", orgID.String(),
    "x-request-id",  requestID,
)
```

## Audit log every cross-tenant denial

Every 403 PERMISSION_DENIED on a cross-tenant resource access must emit an audit log entry. This enables forensic analysis of probing attacks.

```go
if isCrossTenantAccess {
    auditLog.Warn("cross-tenant access attempt",
        "requesting_org_id", requestingOrgID,
        "target_resource_type", "agent",
        "target_resource_id", agentID,
        "request_id", requestID,
    )
}
```
